#compdef SoapySDRUtil
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# pothosware/SoapySDR apps/SoapySDRUtil.cpp `static struct option
# long_options[] = {...}` table + getopt_long_only(argc, argv,
# "", long_options, ...) (empty short-option string = all flags
# are long-only despite each having a single-char enum tag for
# the case-arm dispatch).
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# pothosware SoapySDRUtil R141a — utility tool that ships with the
# SoapySDR cross-vendor SDR API (sister tools `gqrx`/`gnuradio-
# companion`/`inspectrum` already covered in the corpus). Used to
# enumerate, probe, and benchmark SDR devices across hardware
# vendors via the Soapy abstraction layer.

# Note: getopt_long_only with empty short-option string means all
# 15 options below are long-only. The single-char tags in the
# upstream long_options[] table (`'h'`/`'f'`/`'m'`/etc) are used
# only for the case-arm dispatch in `main()` and do NOT shadow as
# `-h`/`-f`/`-m` short aliases per upstream's getopt_long_only
# semantics with `""` short-string.
_arguments -s -S \
  '--help[show help]' \
  '--find=[probe and enumerate connected devices]:filter args:' \
  '--make=[instantiate a device given args; print supported streams]:device args:' \
  '--info[print build info, default config paths, and module loader status]' \
  '--probe=[probe and print info about a device]:device args:' \
  '--watch=[probe + print info; loop to refresh on hot-plug]:device args:' \
  '--check=[run rate-test against a device]:device args:' \
  '--sparse[print less verbose rate-test output]' \
  '--serial=[device-specific serial number to filter by]:serial:' \
  '--args=[per-stream arguments (for --check)]:stream args:' \
  '--rate=[rate to test against (used by --check)]:sample rate Hz:' \
  '--format=[sample format to test against]:format:(CS8 CS12 CS16 CF32 CF64)' \
  '--channels=[channel numbers to test against (comma-separated)]:channel list:' \
  '--direction=[stream direction]:dir:(RX TX)'
